        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 8:02PM EDT by NWS Wilmington OH</headline>
        <description>At 802 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was located over Mount Orab,
moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph, frequent cloud-to-ground
lightning, and very heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Lightning can cause serious injury or
death. Visibility will be poor and hydroplaning is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mount Orab, Williamsburg, Sardinia, Mowrystown, State Route 32 at US
Route 68, Danville in Highland County, Greenbush, State Route 32 at
US Route 62, Locust Ridge, and Buford.

If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a sturdy building.

Motorists should slow down and use extra caution.

When thunder roars, go indoors! Do not stay in the open or seek
shelter under trees when lightning threatens.

To report hazardous weather conditions, go to our website at
weather.gov/iln and submit your report via social media, when you can
do so safely.
</description>
